Often referred to as "the pearl of the Indian Ocean," Sri Lanka is known for its rich biodiversity, large cinnamon and tea exports and stunning natural wonders. It's also a place where the locals shake their heads to say yes and the birthplace of the word "serendipity" in the English language. In Beijing, CGTN's Ioana Gomoi looks for the scents and sights of Sri Lanka by visiting its embassy in China.